'''Michelle Wolf''' (born June 21, 1985) is an American comedian, writer, producer, and television host. She worked as a contributor and writer for ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' and ''[[The Daily Show with Trevor Noah]]''. She spoke as the featured performer at the 2018 [[White House Correspondents' Association#White House Correspondents' Dinner|White House Correspondents' Dinner]]. She hosted the [[Netflix]] comedy [[talk show]] series ''[[The Break with Michelle Wolf]]''.

== Early life and education ==
Wolf was born in [[Hershey, Pennsylvania|Hershey]], [[Pennsylvania]], where she grew up with two older brothers.<ref name="ComicsComic-Interview-2016">{{cite news|url=http://thecomicscomic.com/2016/06/18/book-excerpt-meet-the-regulars-with-sasheer-zamata-and-michelle-wolf-by-joshua-d-fischer/|title=Book Excerpt: Meet The Regulars" with Sasheer Zamata and Michelle Wolf, by Joshua D. Fischer|last=McCarthy|first=Sean L.|date=June 18, 2016|work=The Comic's Comic|access-date=November 10, 2016|ref={{sfnRef|"Meet the Regulars"}}}}</ref><ref name=zarum>{{Cite magazine|last=Zarum|first=Lara|date=November 30, 2017|title=Michelle Wolf Is the Voice Comedy Needs Right Now|url=https://www.villagevoice.com/2017/11/30/michelle-wolf-is-the-voice-comedy-needs-right-now/|magazine=The Village Voice|access-date=March 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Johnson|first=Ted|date=February 23, 2018|title=Michelle Wolf Says She Won’t Hold Back Humor, Even If Trump Attends White House Correspondents’ Dinner|url=https://variety.com/2018/politics/news/michelle-wolf-which-trump-1202708838/|magazine=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=March 4, 2018}}</ref> She graduated from [[Hershey High School (Pennsylvania)|Hershey High School]] in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/celebrities/michelle-wolf-speech-white-house-correspondents-dinner-hersey-pennsylvania-20180430.html|title=Comedian Michelle Wolf ran track in Hershey before she trashed Trump at the White House Correspondents' Dinner|last=Vadala|first=Nick|date=April 30, 2018|work=The Philadelphia Enquirer|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref> She graduated from [[The College of William & Mary]] in 2007, where she majored in [[kinesiology]] and was a member of the [[cardiovascular physiology]] lab.{{sfn|"Meet the Regulars"}}<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.wm.edu/as/kinesiology/faculty/research/mcplab/pastmembers/index.php|title=Past lab members|website=William & Mary|access-date=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bkmag.com/2014/11/19/comedian-michelle-wolf-is-taking-brooklyn-by-stand-up/|title=Comedian Michelle Wolf Is Taking Brooklyn By Stand-Up|last=Eby|first=Margaret|date=November 19, 2014|work=[[Brooklyn Magazine]]|access-date=April 30, 2018}}</ref> She was on the track and field team while in high school and college before an injury caused her to stop competing.{{sfn|"Meet the Regulars"}}

==Career==
Wolf was employed at [[Bear Stearns]] from 2007 to 2008, and later at [[JPMorgan Chase]], working for almost four years in mutual funds and managing accounts<ref>https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/michelle-wolf-things-white-house-correspondents-dinner-host/story?id=53303703</ref> between the two banks.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thewrap.com/how-daily-shows-newest-correspondent-michelle-wolf-went-from-wall-street-to-comedy-central/ | title=How ‘Daily Show’s’ Newest Correspondent Michelle Wolf Went From Wall Street to Comedy Central | work=The Wrap | date=June 24, 2016 | accessdate=September 22, 2016 | author=Otterson, Joe}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://splitsider.com/2014/08/balancing-standup-and-writing-for-late-night-with-michelle-wolf/ | title=Balancing Standup and Writing for ‘Late Night’ with Michelle Wolf | work=Splitsider | date=August 6, 2014 | accessdate=April 9, 2016 | author=Davidson, Phil}}</ref> Around the time of the buyout by JPMorgan, Wolf started improv classes at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]] and the [[Peoples Improv Theater]] (PIT). Her frustration with the imperfect and ephemeral nature of [[improvisational theatre|improv]] and the encouragement from classmates got her to audit a stand-up class at the PIT.<ref name=zarum/> Her first appearance on late-night television was in July 2014, when she went on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]''. She re-appeared on numerous segments on ''Late Night'', often as her fictional persona, "Grown-Up Annie", an adult version of [[Little Orphan Annie]]. She later held additional positions on the same show, including, most recently, as writing supervisor.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/the-daily-show-with-trevor-noah-michelle-wolf-contributor-writer-1201731581/ |title=‘Daily Show With Trevor Noah’ Adds Michelle Wolf As On-Air Contributor & Writer |last=Petski |first=Denise |website=Deadline.com |publication-date=April 4, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/04/comedian-michelle-wolf-joins-the-daily-show-as-wri.html | title=Comedian Michelle Wolf Joins The Daily Show As Writer, Contributor | work=Paste | date=April 4, 2016 | accessdate=April 9, 2016 | author=Blumenfeld, Zach}}</ref> 

In November 2015, [[Comedy Central]] released the entirety of ''Now Hiring'', a web series hosted by Wolf, on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://splitsider.com/2015/11/watch-michelle-wolfs-comedy-central-web-series-now-hiring/ | title=Watch Michelle Wolf’s Comedy Central Web Series ‘Now Hiring’ | work=Splitsider | date=November 9, 2015 | accessdate=April 9, 2016 | author=Wright, Megh}}</ref> Wolf is a regular at the [[Comedy Cellar]] in New York City. In April 2016, she joined ''[[The Daily Show with Trevor Noah]]'' as a contributor.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/151949-who-is-michelle-wolf-this-new-daily-show-correspondent-has-a-lot-to-offer | title=Who Is Michelle Wolf? This New 'Daily Show' Correspondent Has A Lot To Offer | work=Bustle | date=April 4, 2016 | accessdate=April 9, 2016 | author=Lackey, Emily}}</ref> Wolf has said that she learned a lot about comedy working for [[Seth Meyers]] and [[Trevor Noah]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner-host-comedian/|title=Comedian Michelle Wolf says it's "cowardly" for Trump to skip Correspondents' dinner|last=Wax|first=Jamie|date=April 28, 2018|accessdate=April 29, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324150849/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner-host-comedian/|archivedate=April 29, 2018|deadurl=no|publisher=[[CBS News]]}}</ref>

In August 2016, she performed her stand-up show ''So Brave'' at the [[Edinburgh Festival]], which was her first performance outside North America.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2016/aug/02/michelle-wolf-daily-show-comedian-edinburgh |title=Michelle Wolf: 'Four years of Donald Trump jokes will drive me insane' |last=Czajkowski |first=Elise |website=The Guardian |publication-date=August 2, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2017}}</ref>

Wolf's television work in the United Kingdom also includes an appearance on ''[[Live at the Apollo (TV series)|Live At The Apollo]]'' in late 2016 and an appearance as a panelist on the UK comedy game show ''[[8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown]]'' in early 2017, partnering with team captain and British stand-up comedian [[Jon Richardson (comedian)|Jon Richardson]]. She appeared on the same show later on in the year, this time partnering with [[Sean Lock]]. On November 20, 2016, Wolf appeared as a guest on ''[[Frankie Boyle]]'s American Autopsy'' on [[BBC2]], reflecting on the result of the [[2016 US Presidential Election]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b083s663 |title=Frankie Boyle's American Autopsy 2016 |website=[[BBC Two]] |publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref> She also appeared on an episode of ''[[8 Out of 10 Cats]]'' in January 2017, partnering with English [[Association football|footballer]] [[Jermaine Jenas]] and team captain [[Rob Beckett]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/8-out-of-10-cats/episode-guide/series-19 |title=8 Out of 10 Cats - Episode Guide |website=[[All 4]] |publisher=[[Channel Four Television Corporation]] |access-date=October 10, 2017}}</ref> On December 2, 2017, Wolf made her [[HBO]] stand-up debut, ''Michelle Wolf: Nice Lady'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/12/a-nice-lady-michelle-wolf-insists-shes-not.html|title=Michelle Wolf Insists She's Not a Nice Lady|last=Techler|first=Graham|date=December 1, 2017|work=Paste Magazine|access-date=December 4, 2017|language=en}}</ref> which was taped at the [[Skirball Center for the Performing Arts]] in [[New York City]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbo.com/specials/michelle-wolf-nice-lady|title=Michelle Wolf: Nice Lady|website=HBO|language=en|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref> in mid-August 2017,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/12/michelle-wolf-nice-lady-hbo-review-standup-special-1201903044/|title=‘Michelle Wolf: Nice Lady’ is a Great Standup Time Capsule for 2017|last=Greene|first=Steve|date=December 2, 2017|website=IndieWire|language=en|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref> and has received rave reviews highlighting the comedian's ability to keep her jokes fresh while not relying on the news headlines as many comedians have been doing of late.<ref>{{Citation|title=Michelle Wolf: Nice Lady|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/michelle_wolf_nice_lady|language=en|accessdate=December 4, 2017}}</ref><ref name=zarum/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tvinsider.com/650927/michelle-wolf-nice-lady-comedy-special-hbo-interview/|title=Michelle Wolf's Comedy Special 'Nice Lady' Will Have You in Stitches|last=Ratledge|first=Ingela|date=December 2, 2017|work=TV Insider|access-date=December 4, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>

=== 2018 White House Correspondents' Dinner appearance ===
{{excessive detail|section|date=June 2018}}
{{external media| float = right| video1 = [https://www.c-span.org/video/?444555-1/comedian-michelle-wolf-headlines-white-house-correspondents-dinner 2018 White House Correspondents' Dinner, April 28, 2018], [[C-SPAN]]}}

On April 28, 2018, Wolf was the featured entertainer<ref>{{citeweb|last=Johnson|first=Ted|url= https://variety.com/2018/biz/news/michelle-wolf-host-white-house-correspondents-dinner-1202707542/ |title=‘Daily Show’ Contributor Michelle Wolf to Host White House Correspondents’ Dinner| website= Variety| date=February 22, 2018|access-date=May 5, 2018}}</ref> at the [[White House Correspondents' Association#White House Correspondents' Dinner|White House Correspondents' Dinner]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/4/29/17298834/michelle-wolf-jokes-sarah-huckabee-sanders-whcd-maggie-haberman-press-aunt-lydia|title=The Michelle Wolf White House Correspondents’ Dinner controversy, explained |last= Stewart| first= Emily|date=April 30, 2018|work=Vox|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref> U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] did not attend the dinner for the second consecutive year,<ref>{{cite news |last=Sullivan |first=Eileen |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/06/us/politics/trump-white-house-correspondents-dinner.html |title= Trump Will Once Again Skip the White House Correspondents Dinner |work=The New York Times |accessdate=April 14, 2018 |date=April 6, 2018 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120105153224/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/06/us/politics/trump-white-house-correspondents-dinner.html |archivedate=April 14, 2018}}</ref> sending [[Sarah Huckabee Sanders]], the [[White House Press Secretary]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Forgey |first= Quint |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/04/06/trump-plans-to-again-skip-the-white-house-correspondents-dinner-505507 |title= Trump to skip White House Correspondents' Dinner again |work=Politico |accessdate=April 14, 2018 |date=April 6, 2018 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120105153224/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/04/06/trump-plans-to-again-skip-the-white-house-correspondents-dinner-505507 |archivedate= April 14, 2018}}</ref>

Wolf delivered a 19-minute comedy routine<ref>{{citeweb|last=Flynn|first=Megan|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/04/30/trump-scolds-filthy-comedian-michelle-wolf/|title=Trump scolds ‘filthy’ comedian. Head of correspondents group regrets monologue.|website=The Washington Post| date= April 30, 2018|access-date=May 5, 2018}}</ref> and was both praised and criticized for her "harsh and stinging" jokes aimed at the Trump administration—most notably at Sanders—and at the media itself.<ref>{{Cite news| url= http://thehill.com/opinion/white-house/385551-as-republicans-we-cant-laud-kanye-west-for-free-speech-then-denounce|title=As Republicans, we can’t laud Kanye West but denounce Michelle Wolf|last=Bachai|first=Sabrina|date=May 1, 2018|work=The Hill|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2018/04/whca-sanders/559253/|title=Michelle Wolf Does Unto the White House as It Has Done Unto Others| last=Frum|first=David|date=April 30, 2018|work=The Atlantic|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=gessen>{{Cite news| url= https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-michelle-wolf-blasted-open-the-fictions-of-journalism-in-the-age-of-trump|title=How Michelle Wolf Blasted Open the Fictions of Journalism in the Age of Trump|last=Gessen|first=Masha|date=April 30, 2018|work=The New Yorker|access-date=May 2, 2018| language= en| issn=0028-792X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/comedian-michelle-wolf-sparks-fury-debate-roast-correspondents-dinner-n869931|title=Correspondents group criticizes comedian Michelle Wolf for remarks at correspondents' dinner|work=NBC News|access-date=May 3, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Wolf's criticism of journalism has been called "the most consequential monologue so far of the Donald Trump era."<ref name=gessen/> The management of [[C-SPAN Radio|C-SPAN radio]] considered the monologue so risqué that they stopped broadcasting it half-way through, worrying that she might violate FCC indecency guidelines<ref name=":72">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/trump-gives-thumbs-down-to-comic-who-roasted-his-spokeswoman/2018/04/29/e76290c2-4c22-11e8-85c1-9326c4511033_story.html|title=Welcome to the partisan fury, Michelle Wolf|last=Bauder|agency=Associated Press|first=David|date=April 30, 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref> and that they might get fined.<ref name=":8">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2018/5/1/17302684/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner-2018-whcd-reaction|title=Michelle Wolf did exactly the job the White House Correspondents’ Association asked her to do|work=Vox|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref> Wolf’s joke about Sanders using the ashes of lies to create her perfect eye makeup became the most controversial issue among the criticisms aimed at Wolf’s presentation:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/michelle-wolfs-controversial-jokes-white-house-correspondents-dinner/story?id=54831176|title=5 of Michelle Wolf's most controversial jokes at White House correspondents' dinner|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=April 30, 2018| website= ABC News|language=en|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref><blockquote>I actually really like Sarah. I think she’s very resourceful. She burns facts, and then she uses that ash to create a perfect [[Smokey Eyes|smoky eye]]. Like maybe she’s born with it, maybe it’s lies.{{efn|Parallels a [[Maybelline]] slogan, "Maybe she's born with it. Maybe it's Maybelline."}} It’s probably lies.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news| url= https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/4/30/17301436/michelle-wolf-speech-transcript-white-house-correspondents-dinner-sarah-huckabee-sanders| title= Wonder what Michelle Wolf said to make everyone so mad? Read it here.|work=Vox|access-date=2018-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| url= http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2018/04/29/michelle-wolf-doubles-down-on-sarah-sanders-insults-as-journalists-defend-press-secretary.html| title= Michelle Wolf doubles down on Sarah Sanders insults as journalists defend press secretary|last=Lam|first=Katherine|date=2018-04-29|work=Fox News|access-date=2018-05-03|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=C-SPAN|title=Michelle Wolf – Complete Remarks at 2018 White House Correspondents' Dinner (C-SPAN)| date= 2018-04-28|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDbx1uArVOM&feature=youtu.be&t=14m03s|accessdate=2018-05-06}}</ref></blockquote> 

Journalists including [[Maggie Haberman]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref name="eh">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/reliable-source/wp/2018/04/29/the-many-reactions-to-michelle-wolfs-speech-from-trump-saying-she-bombed-to-kumail-nanjianis-support/|title=The many reactions to Michelle Wolf’s speech, from Trump saying she ‘bombed’ to Kumail Nanjiani’s support|last=Heil|first=Emily|date=April 29, 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet| user= maggieNYT| number= 990428993542414336 |title= That @PressSec sat and absorbed intense criticism of her physical appearance, her job performance, and so forth, instead of walking out, on national television, was impressive. | first= Maggie |last= Haberman | date= April 28, 2018| access-date=May 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite news| url= https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/entry/michelle-wolf-hits-back-at-criticism-that-she-attacked-sarah-huckabee-sanders-looks_us_5ae624d8e4b04aa23f242a8a| title= Michelle Wolf Hits Back At Criticism That She Attacked Sarah Huckabee Sanders' Looks|date=April 29, 2018|work=HuffPost Canada|access-date=May 3, 2018| language= en-CA}}</ref> [[Mika Brzezinski]] of [[MSNBC]],<ref name= ":4" /><ref>{{Cite tweet| user= morningmika |title= Watching a wife and mother be humiliated on national television for her looks is deplorable. I have experienced insults about my appearance from the president. All women have a duty to unite when these attacks happen and the WHCA owes Sarah an apology. | number= 990585968825597954| first= Mika |last= Brzezinski | date= April 29, 2018 |access-date=May 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/news/mika-brzezinski-white-house-correspondents-dinner-a-big-win-for-trump/|title=Mika Brzezinski: White House Correspondents Dinner a Big Win for Trump| last= McArdle|first=Mairead|date=April 30, 2018| work= National Review|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| url= https://www.thedailybeast.com/michelle-wolfs-whcd-honesty-is-what-america-needs-right-now|title=Michelle Wolf’s WHCD Honesty Is What America Needs Right Now|last=Ryan|first=Erin Gloria|date=April 30, 2018|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> and [[Andrea Mitchell]] of [[NBC News]],<ref name="eh" /> criticized Wolf on Twitter for targeting Sanders. Ed Henry of [[Fox News]] stated that "[i]t was disgusting, despicable. Sarah Sanders should get an apology from the White House Correspondents Association… and what a contrast to what the president was doing. Talking about issues people actually care about."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hains|first1=Tim|title=FNC's Ed Henry: WH Correspondents Association Should Apologize To Sarah Sanders For "Disgusting" Jokes| url= https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2018/04/29/fncs_ed_henry_wh_correspondents_should_apologize_to_sarah_sanders_for_disgusting_jokes.html|publisher=RealClearPolitics}}</ref> [[CBS News]] executives reportedly considered ending its participation in future dinners, but later changed its stance after the network was assured that the Correspondents' Association would "seriously consider changes to the dinner's format."<ref>{{cite web| last1= Grynbaum| first1=Michael M.|title=Did Michelle Wolf Kill the White House Correspondents’ Dinner?|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/30/business/media/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner.html|work= The New York Times|accessdate=April 30, 2018}}</ref> Former press secretary [[Sean Spicer]] tweeted, "Tonight’s <s>#</s>WHCD was a disgrace"<ref>{{Cite tweet| user= seanspicer| first= Sean| last= Spicer| number= 990430460508549120| title= Tonight’s #WHCD was a disgrace | date= April 28, 2018 |access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/29/business/media/michelle-wolfs-routine-sets-off-a-furor-at-an-annual-washington-dinner.html|title=Michelle Wolf Sets Off a Furor at White House Correspondents’ Dinner|date=April 29, 2018| work= The New York Times|access-date=May 3, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> to which Wolf replied, "Thank you!"<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite tweet| user= michelleisawolf| number= 990432919847079936| title= Thank you!| first= Michelle |last= Wolf | date= April 28, 2018| access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> The next day, Trump called several outside advisors to criticize the comedian,<ref name=":72"/> and he weighed in on Twitter in a series of tweets saying that "so-called comedian"<ref>{{Cite tweet| user= realDonaldTrump| first= Donald| last= Trump| number= 990557728752926725| title= While Washington, Michigan, was a big success, Washington, D.C., just didn’t work. Everyone is talking about the fact that the White House Correspondents Dinner was a very big, boring bust...the so-called comedian really “bombed.” @greggutfeld should host next year! @PeteHegseth | date= April 29, 2018| access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> and the "filthy 'comedian' totally bombed"<ref>{{Cite tweet| user= realDonaldTrump| first= Donald| last= Trump| number= 990782291667488768| title= The White House Correspondents’ Dinner was a failure last year, but this year was an embarrassment to everyone associated with it. The filthy “comedian” totally bombed (couldn’t even deliver her lines-much like the Seth Meyers weak performance). Put Dinner to rest, or start over!| date= April 29, 2018|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> and called for the dinner to be put to rest or start over.<ref name="flynn" /> He later added the dinner was "DEAD as we know it."<ref name="flynn" /><ref name=":9">{{Cite tweet| user= realDonaldTrump| first= Donald| last= Trump| number= 990926480329859073| title= The White House Correspondents’ Dinner is DEAD as we know it. This was a total disaster and an embarrassment to our great Country and all that it stands for. FAKE NEWS is alive and well and beautifully represented on Saturday night!| date= April 30, 2018 |access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> 

Michelle Wolf questioned her critics from the media: "Why are you guys making this about Sarah’s looks? I said she burns facts and uses the ash to create a *perfect* smoky eye. I complimented her eye makeup and her ingenuity of materials."<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite tweet| user= michelleisawolf| number= 990610206425042946 |first= Michelle |last= Wolf | title= Why are you guys making this about Sarah’s looks? I said she burns facts and uses the ash to create a *perfect* smoky eye. I complimented her eye makeup and her ingenuity of materials. | date= April 29, 2018|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> In an interview with [[Terry Gross]] on [[NPR]], Wolf said that the joke wasn't about Sanders' looks at all, it was about her lies, and there isn't really a need to defend it in the first place.<ref name=":12">{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/05/01/607262463/comic-michelle-wolf-responds-to-backlash-im-glad-i-stuck-to-my-guns| title= Comic Michelle Wolf Responds To Backlash: 'I'm Glad I Stuck To My Guns'| work= NPR.org| access-date=May 2, 2018|language=en}}</ref> She said she did not attack any of the women's physical appearances unlike some male politicians such as [[Mitch McConnell]]'s neck or [[Chris Christie]]'s weight, but "as a woman, I have access to hit women in a way that men might not be able to hit them with jokes." Talking about her performance, "I wouldn't change a single word that I said. I'm very happy with what I said, and I'm glad I stuck to my guns."<ref name=":12" /> 

Other journalists, including [[Jacob Soboroff]] of NBC News, [[Joan Walsh]] of [[CNN]], [[Amanda Hess]] of ''The New York Times'', and [[Wesley Lowery]] of ''[[The Washington Post]]'', tweeted their support for Wolf and took the [[White House Correspondents' Association]] (WHCA) to task for the statement issued by its president, Margaret Talev.<ref name="amatulli">{{citeweb|last=Amatulli|first=Jenna|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/journalists-rebuke-of-michelle-wolf-doesnt-celebrate-press-freedom_us_5ae70b2fe4b02baed1bc4dd8|title=Journalists Push Back On Correspondents’ Association’s Response To Michelle Wolf|website=Huffington Post|date=April 30, 2018|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref><ref name="flynn">{{citeweb|last=Flynn|first=Meagan|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/04/30/trump-scolds-filthy-comedian-michelle-wolf/|title=Trump scolds ‘filthy’ comedian. Head of correspondents group regrets monologue.|website=The Washington Post|date=April 30, 2018|access-date=April 30, 2018}}</ref> Talev wrote that the program "was meant to offer a unifying message about [the WHCA's] common commitment to a vigorous and free press while honoring civility, great reporting and scholarship winners, not to divide people,"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2018/04/29/michelle-wolf-sarah-huckabee-sanders-kellyanne-conway-whcd-white-house-correspondents-dinner/562535002/|title=White House Correspondents' Dinner: Michelle Wolf obliterates Sarah Huckabee Sanders|last=Jensen|first=Erin|date=April 29, 2018|work=USA Today|access-date=April 29, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name="samuels">{{cite web|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/media/385442-white-house-correspondents-association-michelle-wolfs-routine-not-in-the|title=White House Correspondents' Association: Michelle Wolf's routine 'not in the spirit' of our mission|last=Samuels|first=Brett|date=April 29, 2018|website=The Hill|access-date=April 30, 2018}}</ref> and that Wolf’s "monologue was not in the spirit of that mission."<ref name="amatulli"/><ref name="flynn"/><ref name="samuels"/> [[James Poniewozik]], writing for ''The New York Times,'' criticized the WHCA for disavowing Wolf, saying that she was "defending the mission of the [[White House press corps|White House press]]: sticking up for the truth. Michelle Wolf had the WHCA’s back Saturday night, even if it didn’t have hers the day after."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/30/arts/television/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner.html|title=Michelle Wolf Did Her Job. It’s the Correspondents’ Dinner That Is the Problem.|last=Poniewozik|first=James|date=April 30, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> ''[[The New Yorker]]''<nowiki/>'s [[Masha Gessen]] was particularly impressed with Wolf's criticism of journalism, praising her for how she "exposed the obscenity of the fictions" of "The Age of Trump".<ref name="gessen"/>

Several comedians also came to Wolf's defense, including [[Jimmy Kimmel]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://people.com/politics/stars-defend-michelle-wolf-sarah-huckabee-sanders-jokes-white-house-correspondents-dinner/|title=Jimmy Kimmel and More Stars Defend Michelle Wolf Over Sarah Sanders Jokes|last=McAfee|first=Tierney|date=April 30, 2018|work=People|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> [[Trevor Noah]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/trevor-noah-fires-ex-daily-show-writer-michelle-wolf-whcd-article-1.3964615|title=Trevor Noah 'fires' ex-'Daily Show' writer Michelle Wolf over White House Correspondents' Dinner|last=Feldman|first=Kate|date=May 1, 2018|work=New York Daily News|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> [[Seth Meyers]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/seth-meyers-defends-michelle-wolf-sarah-huckabee-sanders-got-off-easy|title=Seth Meyers Defends Michelle Wolf: ‘Sarah Huckabee Sanders Got Off Easy’|last=Wilstein|first=Matt|date=May 1, 2018|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> [[Adam Conover]],<ref>{{Cite news| url= https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/30/opinion/michelle-wolf-white-house-correspondents-dinner.html|title=Michelle Wolf Did What Comedians Are Supposed to Do| last= Conover|first=Adam|date=April 30, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> [[Dave Chappelle]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/nation/dave-chappelle-says-michelle-wolf-nailed-it-at-white-house-correspondents-dinner| title= Dave Chappelle says Michelle Wolf 'nailed it' at White House Correspondents Dinner|last=Jacobson|first=Murrey|date=April 30, 2018|website=PBS NewsHour |publisher= PBS |language=en-US|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref> [[Kathy Griffin]],<ref>{{Cite tweet| user= kathygriffin| number= 990651595905028096| first= Kathy | last= Griffin | date= April 29, 2018| title= A) Ok I have some thoughts on @michelleisawolf's act and the reaction to it from members of the press and other DC insiders. For the record, I was in the room last night. @michelleisawolf's set was great. She was hilarious and confident. | access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> [[Guy Branum]],<ref name=":0" /> and [[Anthony Atamanuik]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news| url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/many-criticized-michelle-wolfs-correspondents-dinner-set-but-comedians-had-her-back/2018/04/30/a44b0372-4ca5-11e8-84a0-458a1aa9ac0a_story.html |title= Michelle Wolf’s correspondents’ dinner set made Washington uncomfortable. But comedians have her back.| last= Izadi| first= Elahe|date=April 30, 2018|work=Washington Post| access-date= May 1, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref> [[Stephen Colbert]], who was the featured entertainer at [[Stephen Colbert at the 2006 White House Correspondents' Dinner|the 2006 edition of the event]], joked on ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert|The Late Show]]'', "This is the correspondents’ dinner, celebrating the freedom of speech. You can’t just say whatever you want!"<ref>{{cite news| last= Yahr| first= Emily| url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/reliable-source/wp/2018/05/01/late-night-hosts-ridicule-the-outrage-over-michelle-wolfs-correspondents-dinner-speech/|title=Late-night hosts ridicule the outrage over Michelle Wolf’s correspondents’ dinner speech|website=The Washington Post|date=May 1, 2018| access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=The Late Show with Stephen Colbert| title= Stephen Colbert (The Other One) On Michelle Wolf's WHCD Speech| date=May 1, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i8gE20TW1n4&t=5m2s|accessdate=May 3, 2018}}</ref> [[Nell Scovell]] writing for ''[[Vulture (magazine)|Vulture]]'' criticized journalists Haberman, Brzezinski, Mitchell for what Scovell called a "manufactured [[catfight]]" between Wolf and Sanders. Describing the ensuing controversy, Scovell wrote, "[w]omen, comedians, and the media all grabbed each other’s hair and threw each other to the floor while men watched and cheered."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2018/04/white-house-correspondents-dinner-should-go-on.html|title=Why the White House Correspondents’ Dinner Should Go On|last=Scovell|first=Nell|work=Vulture|access-date=May 6, 2018|language=en}}</ref>

=== ''The Break with Michelle Wolf'' ===
{{Main|The Break with Michelle Wolf}}
Michelle Wolf hosted a weekly [[Netflix]] talk show, ''[[The Break with Michelle Wolf]]'', which premiered May 27, 2018 and was discontinued on August 18, 2018. It will "take a break from the seriousness of late-night comedy" and "instead of making the news fun, she’ll make fun of everything and everybody. There will be no preaching or political agenda—unless it’s funny."<ref name="SeriesOrder1">{{cite web|last1=Petski|first1=Denise|title=‘Daily Show’ Writer Michelle Wolf Lands Netflix Talk Show| url= http://deadline.com/2018/02/michelle-wolf-netflix-talk-show-the-daily-show-late-night-with-seth-meyers-1202286496/|website= Deadline.com | accessdate= February 14, 2018|date=February 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.netflix.com/title/80239459|title=The Break with Michelle Wolf |website= Netflix.com| access-date=May 4, 2018}}</ref> She is also an executive producer for the show.<ref name= "SeriesOrder1"/><ref>{{cite web| last1= Otterson| first1= Joe|title=‘Daily Show’ Contributor Michelle Wolf Lands Netflix Late-Night Series| url= https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/daily-show-michelle-wolf-netflix-late-night-series-1202695215/|website=Variety|accessdate=February 14, 2018|date=February 12, 2018}}</ref> Netflix released the trailer to coincide with her appearance at 2018 White House Correspondents' Dinner.<ref>{{Cite news| url= https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/michelle-wolf-netflix-show-trailer_us_5ae75e87e4b04aa23f25ea27|title=Michelle Wolf's Netflix Show Trailer Came Out This Weekend Too| last= McDonald| first= Andy| date= April 30, 2018|work=Huffington Post|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| url= http://fortune.com/2018/04/30/netflix-white-house-correspondents-dinner-michelle-wolf-whcd-the-break/|title=Why Netflix Could Be the Big Winner (or Loser) After Saturday's White House Correspondent's Dinner| last= Morris| first= Chris| date= April 30, 2018|work=Fortune|access-date=May 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Netflix ordered a 10-episode season that premered in May 2018 and aired over 10 weeks, with the series finale on July 29, 2018.  According to [[Deadline Hollywood]] the show did not draw enough of a viewership to secure a renewal.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/the-break-with-michelle-wolf-the-joel-mchale-show-canceled-netflix-1202447909/ |title=‘The Break With Michelle Wolf’ & ‘The Joel McHale Show’ Canceled By Netflix |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=2018-08-17 |work=Deadline |access-date=2018-08-18 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Wolf is an avid runner. She has run [[marathon]]s, and in 2018 completed a {{convert|50|mi|adj=on}} [[ultramarathon]] at the [[Bonneville Salt Flats]] in [[Utah]].<ref>{{cite interview| first= Michelle| last= Wolf| work= Late Night With Seth Meyers| publisher= NBC| title= Season 5, Episode 102| interviewer= Seth Myers| date= May 9, 2018}}</ref>

